<p>
    By the end of 2017, in a climate of turmoil with bad financials and significant layoffs, which included a CEO and top management change, it was clear to everyone that <em>Ericsson</em> needed to do something to not only refresh the brand but also to pave the way for the impending arrival of 5G.
</p>
<p>
    To quickstart, what was seen internally as a transformational journey, a new brand was commissioned from <a href="https://www.stockholmdesignlab.se/work/ericsson" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Stockholm Design Lab</a>, which had previously proven themselves tackling the <em>Volvo</em> rebrand. es with the latest Volvo rebrand. We dubbed the project <em>Ericsson TwoDotZero</em>, and my team (Ericsson Customer Experience) was involved from the very beginning because of our insights gained from supporting and reviewing the product UX across the entire portfolio.
</p>

