<h2>A User Experience first brand</h2>

<p>
    If we wanted the new brand to have a real transformational and galvanizing effect, we needed to flip the Ericsson gamebook around. We focused on creating design (not designer) principles that would be at the core of everything the company did to move forward into the future.
</p>
<p>
    In the end, three brand principles were adopted as mantras that everyone should mentally recite. <em>Focused simplicity</em>, <em>Delight means performance</em>, and <em>Coherence inside out</em>.
</p>
<p>
    Based on these, we generated specific UX principles to guide designers and developers. I called this the <em>Ericsson UX 2.0</em> vision and presented it during the <em>Ericsson Leadership Summit 2017</em>, an event that packed Globen with the top worldwide managers.
</p>

